Media notes: Still from a video--foraging on insects kicked up by our feet.

Locality: Westland Tai Poutini NP--Franz Joseph Glacier Walk

Observation Details: saw many fantails along the Ngā Tapuwae o Toi Trail
saw many fantails along the Ngā Tapuwae o Toi Trail

I was absolutely amazed to discover that, unlike the tales of the Pilotbird and the Lyrebird back home in Australia, the Fantail's fondness for Saddlebacks is in fact entirely true; most of the Saddlebacks had one or two Fantails excitedly flitting from perch to perch beside them, hoping for any morsels thrown out by the devastation wreaked on the bark and leaf litter by their Saddleback friends!!!

I was very happy and slightly perplexed to find three Fantails bunched up on a single branch, all singing together at the tops of their lungs; all were adults, so I have no idea what this could've been about!!
